"{\"abstract\":\"Many applications of Bayesian data analysis involve sensitive information such as personal documents or medical records, motivating methods which ensure that privacy is protected. We introduce a general privacy-preserving framework for Variational Bayes (VB), a widely used optimization-based Bayesian inference method. Our framework respects differential privacy, the gold-standard privacy criterion. The iterative nature of variational Bayes presents a challenge since iterations increase the amount of noise needed to ensure privacy. We overcome this by combining: (1) an improved composition method, called the moments accountant, and (2) the privacy amplification effect of subsampling mini-batches from large-scale data in stochastic learning. We empirically demonstrate the effectiveness of our method on LDA topic models, evaluated on Wikipedia. In the full paper we extend our method to a broad class of models, including Bayesian logistic regression and sigmoid belief networks [Park et al., 2020].\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"40289577\",\"name\":\"J. Foulds\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/40289577\"},{\"authorId\":\"49360101\",\"name\":\"Mijung Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/49360101\"},{\"authorId\":\"38120884\",\"name\":\"K. Chaudhuri\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/38120884\"},{\"authorId\":\"1678311\",\"name\":\"M. Welling\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1678311\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":220483376,\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2020/705\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":false,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"7e9872c463eb51494d047c43b43da043eb297188\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":\"1607.00133\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"51284110\",\"name\":\"M. Abadi\"},{\"authorId\":\"1396184193\",\"name\":\"Andy Chu\"},{\"authorId\":\"153440022\",\"name\":\"Ian J. Goo